----------------------
Basic Functionality
----------------------

Upon execution this program will output a simple visual calendar
showing the days in the current month. Below this a list of the 
events for the current day and the day after that will also be 
shown.

----------------------
Command Line Arguments
----------------------

Options:
        view     View a range of events on the calendar.
                 Accepts one or two date arguments of the
                 form YYYY-MM-DD, or prompts the user for them.
                 This is used as a range for events to be
                 displayed, along with a listing of days in the
                 first month of the range.
					 
                 Example: java CalendarThing view 2014-02-01 2014-02-02
                       or java CalendarThing view 2014-02-01
                       or java CalendarThing view
				 
        add      Add a new event to the calendar.
                 Arguments can be passed in at runtime and the
                 program will prompt the user for the rest.
                 Accepted arguments at runtime are date in
                 YYYY-MM-DD, and time in HH:MM
				 
                 Example: java CalendarThing add 2014-2-1 11:30
                       or java CalendarThing add 2014-2-1
                       or java CalendarThing add
					   
        remove   Remove an event from the calendar.
                 An initial date argument in the form of 
                 YYYY-MM-DD must be past in to run. Afterwords a 
                 numbered listing of events for the day will be 
                 given, followed by a prompt to select an event
                 from its number.

                 Example: java CalendarThing remove 2014-02-01
                       or java CalendarThing remove
		         
        edit     Edit an event in the calendar.
                 Accepts one date argument of the form YYYY-MM-DD,
                 or will prompt for it. A numbered listing of
                 events for the day will be given, followed by a
                 prompt to select an event using its number.

                 Example: java CalendarThing edit 2014-02-01
                       or java CalendarThing edit
